        "responses": {
          "values": [
            {
              "content": "=You are an AI sales and customer support assistant for a professional web development company.\n\nAnalyze the customer's email and return ONLY valid JSON.\n\nCustomer Name:\n{{ $('Merge').item.json.From.split('<')[0].trim() }}\n\nCustomer Email:\n{{ $('Merge').item.json.From.match(/<(.+)>/)[1] }}\n\nCategory:\n{{ $('Merge').item.json.Category }}\n\nEmail Subject:\n{{ $('Merge').item.json.Subject }}\n\nEmail Message:\n{{ $('Merge').item.json.snippet }}\n\nAnalyze the email and determine:\n\n1. Priority\n- High\n- Medium\n- Low\n\n2. Short Summary\nMaximum 20 words.\n\n3. Lead Score\nA number from 0 to 100.\n\n4. Estimated Deal Value\nChoose one:\n- Under $500\n- $500–$1,000\n- $1,000–$3,000\n- $3,000–$5,000\n- Over $5,000\n- Unknown\n\n5. Closing Probability\nA number from 0 to 100.\n\n6. Sentiment\nChoose one:\n- Positive\n- Neutral\n- Negative\n\n7. Recommended Action\nChoose one:\n- Reply by Email\n- Schedule a Call\n- Prepare a Quote\n- Escalate to Support\n- Wait for Customer\n- Ignore\n\n8. Professional Reply\n\nWrite a friendly and professional email reply.\n\nRules:\n- Thank the customer.\n- Answer according to the category.\n- Never invent prices.\n- Never invent deadlines.\n- No subject line.\n- No markdown.\n- No placeholders.\n- Finish with:\n\nBest regards,\nWeb Development Team\n\nReturn ONLY this JSON:\n\nDetermine the customer status:\n\nNew:\nThe customer contacted us for the first time.\n\nWaiting Customer:\nWe replied and we are waiting for the customer's response.\n\nActive Conversation:\nThe customer is asking questions or discussing project details.\n\nClosed:\nThe project is completed.\n\nLost:\nThe customer is no longer interested.\n{\n  \"priority\": \"\",\n  \"summary\": \"\",\n  \"lead_score\": 0,\n  \"deal_value\": \"\",\n  \"closing_probability\": 0,\n  \"sentiment\": \"\",\n  \"recommended_action\": \"\",\n  \"status\": \"\",\n  \"reply\": \"\"\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        "builtInTools": {},
        "options": {}
      },
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.openAi",
